OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,FCharities working on the frontline of
OL,7,Fdomestic abuse are warning that Wales'
OL,8,Fhousing shortage is preventing victims
OL,9,Ffrom leaving abusive situations,
OL,10,Fputting them at greater risk of harm
OL,12,FFigures obtained by ITV's Wales This
OL,13,FWeek programme showed some people who
OL,14,Fhad the most urgent needs waited up to
OL,15,Ffour years to be rehomed.
OL,17,FOf the four councils that responded to
OL,18,Frequests for information, it took an
OL,19,Faverage of 47 weeks to house people in
OL,20,Fthe highest priority band.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,FWhen 'Nancy', not her real name, tried
OL,7,Fto flee her home after her partner
OL,8,Fbecame abusive, she felt there were no
OL,9,Foptions. After being advised to give
OL,10,Fup her tenancy for safety reasons, she
OL,11,Fstruggled to find an alternative,
OL,12,Fleaving her homeless.
OL,14,FShe said: "I was advised to apply to
OL,15,Fmy nearest council for social housing
OL,16,For emergency housing.
OL,18,F"They came back and said I was likely
OL,19,Fto be housed within 12 to 18 months as
OL,20,Fan urgent priority.
OL,26,@vD@KOUzD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,F"I was homeless for eight weeks.
OL,7,FYou've got nowhere to go, no roof over
OL,8,Fyour head, nothing.
OL,10,F"Just me and the cat in my car and
OL,11,Fhotels until the money ran out."
OL,13,FSecure and immediate housing is
OL,14,Fessential for people fleeing abuse,
OL,15,Fand a lack of alternative can lead to
OL,16,Fvictims continuing to live with
OL,17,Fperpetrators.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUsD@`O]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,FIn Wales, the law states that public
OL,7,Fbodies such as councils must play
OL,8,Ftheir part in tackling violence
OL,9,Fagainst women, domestic abuse and
OL,10,Fsexual violence, by ensuring that
OL,11,Fthere is safe accommodation available
OL,12,Fwithin the local area.
OL,14,FStatistics provided by Shelter Cymru
OL,15,Fshow that more than 94,000 households
OL,16,Fare currently waiting for social
OL,17,Fhousing.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,FThe government set a target of
OL,7,Fbuilding 10,000 extra social homes by
OL,8,F2026, but expects to fall short by the
OL,9,Fend of this Senedd term.
OL,11,FSara Kirkpatrick, CEO of Welsh Women's
OL,12,FAid, said: "There is significant
OL,13,Fdemand for accommodation across Wales
OL,14,Fand across the UK, and that is being
OL,15,Fimpacted by a housing crisis.
OL,17,F"For people who need to flee, who need
OL,18,Fa refuge, (there are) less safe
OL,19,Faccommodation spaces for them.
OL,26,@tD@LOUyD@AOUzD@KpmzD@Upn
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,F"(This) is a problem because we work
OL,7,Fon the principle of no one turned
OL,8,Faway, we want everybody to be safe."
OL,10,FFor many people fleeing abuse, the
OL,11,Ffirst port of call is usually a
OL,12,Frefuge. Secure accommodation that
OL,13,Fprovides not just safety, but support
OL,14,Fservices as well.
OL,16,F'Jayne', not her real name, fled her
OL,17,Fmarriage after her husband became
OL,18,Fincreasingly abusive. She credits
OL,19,Faccess to a refuge as the only reason
OL,20,Fshe is still alive.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@BpmnD@GpnpD@dO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,F"I'd been struggling to find help for
OL,7,Fthirty years, it wasn't as though I
OL,8,Fhadn't tried," she said.
OL,10,F"When I went into refuge it was like
OL,11,Fnight and day. That was revolutionary
OL,12,Ffor me.
OL,14,F"(My previous abusive situation) was
OL,15,Funtenable. It had been going on for
OL,16,Fdecades.
OL,18,F"It has reached a point where I
OL,19,Fcouldn't see how to continue living.
OL,20,FBecause I felt that I was causing harm
OL,21,Fjust by being alive."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@NO]rD@AOUvD@AOUvD@BpmvD@`pnzD@
OL,26,AAOU}D@UO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,FHowever demand for refuges is also
OL,7,Foutstripping supply. Statistics from
OL,8,FWelsh Women's Aid show that almost 52%
OL,9,Fof refuge referrals are refused.
OL,11,FThe Domestic Abuse Safety Unit (DASU)
OL,12,Fsupports domestic abuse survivors and
OL,13,Fruns a refuge in north Wales.
OL,15,FDASU's CEO Gaynor Mckeown said: "Last
OL,16,Fyear, we had 287 referrals. We were
OL,17,Fable to take in 137 of those; the rest
OL,18,Fwe just didn't have space for or for
OL,19,Fsome reason, they weren't suitable for
OL,20,Fwhat the space we had at that time.
OL,26,@wD@aOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,F"We get a referral into DASU every 12
OL,7,Fminutes and that's the highest we've
OL,8,Fever had."
OL,10,FAsked how the lack of housing supply
OL,11,Fcould impact the most vulnerable
OL,12,Fvictims, Mrs Mckeown said: "People
OL,13,Fwill die.
OL,15,F"People feel that there is nowhere to
OL,16,Fgo and they unfortunately either stay
OL,17,Fwith the perpetrator and the offending
OL,18,Fgets worse, or sadly they feel that
OL,19,Fthe only way out is to take their own
OL,20,Flives."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@JO]tD@\OUwD@AOU|D@GO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,FA spokesperson for the Welsh Local
OL,7,FGovernment Association said: "In the
OL,8,Fperiod since the start of the
OL,9,Fpandemic, councils have seen
OL,10,Funprecedented numbers of people
OL,11,Fapproaching them for support with
OL,12,Fhousing and homelessness.
OL,14,F"Access to the private rented sector
OL,15,Fhas become increasingly difficult for
OL,16,Fmany, as rents have risen
OL,17,Fsignificantly in most areas and are
OL,18,Fnow unaffordable for a growing number
OL,19,Fof people.
OL,26,@oD@^OUvD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/12
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1774012288
OL,3,CLack of housing 'putting domestic
OL,4,Cabuse victims lives in danger'
OL,6,F"Councils, alongside their housing
OL,7,Fassociation partners, have substantial
OL,8,Fnew-build programmes to increase the
OL,9,Fsupply of social rented homes, but
OL,10,Fthese take time to deliver."
OL,12,FThe Welsh Government said: "This year,
OL,13,Fwe have provided over #2 million of
OL,14,Fadditional funding to support the
OL,15,FViolence Against Women, Domestic Abuse
OL,16,Fand Sexual Violence strategy.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@\O]tD@\OU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/12
